The paper deals with a matching problem involving self-interested agents, which is a classic topic in game theory (cs.GT). The problem also involves designing a mechanism to maximize efficiency, which is a common theme in algorithmic game theory (cs.AI). The use of graphs and vertices suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the model to kidney exchange suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper deals with designing mechanisms that are strategyproof, which is a key concept in mechanism design (cs.EC).
